begin_memory_text: We introduced our names and where we lived. I never felt hesitated any moment to share the information with her. I felt like that we both definitely trust each other.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about our families, what we are doing for a living, and what we are doing for fun. We talked about everything like old friends talking things.
end_memory_text: At the end of our conversation, we talked about how we can do our best to protect ourselves and others during this difficult time. we give our best wishes to each other.
rest_of_day_open: I would say I will enjoy the rest week. I will work more harder during the workday since I know everybody works very hard right now. At weekends, I plan to spend more time with my family, and cook some dishes I am good at for them. I can not wait for that right now.
critical_positive: The things working really well in this conversation are that we never felt a moment that we lack a topic to continue the conversation. Everything went smoothly just like water flows. Our topics ranges from family, working, education to fun things we like. I would say that it is very pleasant to talk with her.
critical_negative: I could not think of anything that did not work out. Our interaction is natural and smooth just like two friends talking about everything we know and I can feel we care about each other. If I have to say, I would like to go further deep about each topic.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we live and what we do for work. He is a researcher and lives in Florida. We also talked about our family and COVID.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about school and online learning. He has a daughter who is 12 years old and who is doing school online. We talked some about his wife, who is a rehab nurse.
end_memory_text: We talked some about COVID and how our states are dealing with reopening. We also talked more about his daughter and her online learning. She was having a hard time adapting to learning on the computer.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of the week should go well. I have to homeschool my son and teacher online. I am a single mom. I do DoorDash on weekends so that I can make extra money to pay for my son's therapy. My son and I will also get to spend time with my mom this weekend, which is always fun. If I have time, I will go and vote early. This week should be good.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is that I teach middle school and his daughter is in middle school. We were able to discuss this. I also think that COVID is easy to talk about because it is something that everyone is dealing with. He was also very nice, so that made it easy.
critical_negative: I felt very nervous during the conversation. I am not very good at having conversations with people, so I feel like I asked too many questions. I also think we didn't have a great deal in common so I am not sure if we were able to connect on anything. I feel like I did not do a good job.
